                                          Func<T,T> f)
        Applies a comprehension function to each element of a given list and manipulates the list according to this function. If the comprehension function returns null, the element is removed from the list.
        Parameters:
        list - input list
        f - comprehension function

      • map

        public static <In,Out> java.util.List<Out> map(java.util.List<In> in,
                                               Func<In,Out> f)
        Applies a comprehension function to each element of a given list and returns a new list (with those modification) as a result. The given input list is not modified. If the comprehension function returns null the according list element is not included in the returned list.
        Parameters:
        in - input list
        f - comprehension function
        Returns:
        new list that is a comprehension of in (the input list)
